1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with predicting the location of hands and objects in video frames using convolutional neural networks.
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper involves designing a new neural network architecture for predicting future scene representations.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category as the paper involves regression and prediction using neural networks.
4. cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely but still possible sub-category as the paper's approach could be applied to robotics applications involving object detection and tracking.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a less likely but possible sub-category as the paper deals with predicting future frames in videos.
